Mustapha Rabe, representing Mai’adua  Constituency in Katsina State House of Assembly, has commenced the  disbursement of N4.8 million to people in his constituency for  Eid-el-Fitr celebration. Mustapha (APC) told the News Agency
of Nigeria (NAN) on Thursday that the gesture, which also included 300
bags of rice, was to assist orphans and the less privileged in Mai’adua. He said that each of the 500
beneficiaries, which cut across the 10 wards, would get N5,000 each,
while the remaining money would be shared by APC stakeholders in the
constituency. He urged the people to celebrate with
modesty and ensure they practice proper hygiene and social distancing
during the celebration. He enjoined the people to use
Eid-el-Fitr to offer special prayers to Almighty Allah to overpower the
COVID-19 pandemic in Katsina, Nigeria and the world at large. (NAN) Suleiman idris is a graduate of Fed Univ of Tech Minna (BTECH Mathematics/Comp Science), Specialist in ICT Support Services. also proficient in use of  online journalism tools & Social media management.  I currently serve as I.T Officer with Africa's Largest TV Network NTA